The article discusses the issuance of fact sheets on October 1, 2018, regarding the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (USMCA). President Donald J. Trump claims that the USMCA is a great deal for all three countries, addressing the deficiencies and mistakes of NAFTA. He believes that it will open up markets for farmers and manufacturers, reduce trade barriers for the US, and foster competition among the three nations. The article also mentions that President Trump is fulfilling his promise to deliver a modern and rebalanced trade deal with Mexico and Canada. The USMCA is said to benefit businesses, farmers, and workers, while modernizing the trade relationship with Canada and Mexico.